    <div class="explainer">
      <h2>Understanding Blox Fruits Trade Values</h2>
      <p>In the expansive and highly competitive ecosystem of Blox Fruits on Roblox, trading is one of the most vital mechanics. Whether you are a newcomer looking to upgrade from a basic elemental fruit or a veteran assembling a collection of top-tier Mythicals, mastering the economy is non-negotiable. Unfortunately, the internal systems provided by the game do not reflect the actual reality of community-driven market dynamics.</p>

      <p>This Blox Fruits Trade Calculator serves as an essential utility for bridging the massive disconnect between what a fruit costs in Beli (the in-game currency) and its true, liquid value among the player base. By modeling both the strict mechanical requirements and the fluid community valuations, this tool protects you from accepting terrible deals disguised as mathematically fair trades.</p>

      <h3>The Beli Value vs. Community Value Disconnect</h3>
      <p>To understand why a calculator is necessary, you must first understand the two distinct layers of valuation within the game: Beli Value and Community Trade Value.</p>

      <p><strong>Beli Value</strong> is the static, developer-assigned price of a fruit when purchased directly from the Blox Fruit Dealer. For instance, the Gravity fruit has a massive Beli value of 2,500,000. Conversely, the Buddha fruit holds a modest Beli value of 1,200,000. If you were strictly adhering to the in-game prices, Gravity should be worth more than twice as much as Buddha.</p>

      <p>However, <strong>Community Trade Value</strong> completely ignores these static numbers. Community value is dictated entirely by a fruit's utility in PvP combat, its effectiveness in grinding levels, its visual appeal, and its overall rarity. Returning to the previous example: Buddha is widely regarded as the absolute best fruit for grinding and raiding due to its massive hitbox and damage reduction when awakened. Gravity, despite its high cost, is largely considered sluggish and ineffective in both PvP and PvE scenarios. As a result, the community trade value of a Buddha is astronomically higher than that of a Gravity.</p>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <strong>The Golden Rule of Trading:</strong><br/>
        Never accept a trade solely because the Beli values match. Always evaluate the trade based on the community demand and utility of the fruits involved.
      </div>

      <h3>The In-Game 40% Value Difference Rule</h3>
      <p>While community value dictates the fairness of a trade, the game's internal mechanics still impose a strict barrier known as the Maximum Value Difference rule. To prevent massive wealth transfers (or cross-trading exploitation), the Blox Fruits trading system requires that the total Beli value of the items offered by one player must be within 40% of the total Beli value offered by the other player.</p>

      <p>For example, if you offer a fruit worth 1,000,000 Beli, the other player must offer fruits that total at least 600,000 Beli. If they offer less, the game's UI will block the transaction entirely, presenting an "Value difference is too high" error.</p>

      <p>This creates a paradoxical challenge for high-end trading. If you want to trade a highly sought-after, low-Beli fruit for an undesirable, high-Beli fruit (perhaps you are trading to a collector), the system will block you. To circumvent this, traders often use "adds"—low-demand fruits thrown into a trade exclusively to pad the Beli value and trick the system into allowing the transaction to proceed. Our calculator automatically checks this 40% rule simultaneously alongside the community value calculation, ensuring your proposed trade is actually possible to execute in-game.</p>

      <h3>How Values Fluctuate</h3>
      <p>The Blox Fruits economy is incredibly volatile, reacting swiftly to announcements, updates, and community sentiment.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Game Updates and Awakenings:</strong> When the developers announce that an older fruit is receiving an "Awakening" (a massive buff to its visual and damage profile), the community value of that fruit will spike immediately as players rush to stockpile it before the update drops.</li>
        <li><strong>Reworks:</strong> Complete structural reworks of fruits (such as the highly anticipated Dragon rework) cause massive, long-term shifts in value as players speculate on the new power levels.</li>
        <li><strong>New Fruit Releases:</strong> The release of a new Mythical fruit (like Kitsune or T-Rex) completely disrupts the top end of the market. New fruits carry an immense "hype tax," trading for far more than their mechanical utility dictates simply because players want to experience the new content.</li>
        <li><strong>Content Creator Showcases:</strong> High-profile Roblox YouTubers frequently influence the market. If a popular creator publishes a video highlighting an overpowered combo using a mid-tier fruit, demand for that fruit will temporarily surge.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Methodology Behind Our Estimator</h3>
      <p>Maintaining an accurate calculator requires balancing static in-game data with dynamic community sentiment. The underlying JavaScript logic driving this tool functions through a multi-tiered evaluation process.</p>

      <p>First, the calculator maintains an internal dictionary mapping every fruit to both its static Beli cost and an estimated community trade value index. This index is a simplified numerical representation derived from ongoing analyses of major trading Discord servers, community tier lists, and successful trade logs.</p>

      <p>When you select fruits for "Your Offer" and "Their Offer," the script aggregates the values on both sides. It performs the rigid 40% Beli difference check mathematically by comparing the absolute difference between the two total Beli pools against the required threshold. Simultaneously, it compares the aggregate community trade values. The result is then evaluated to determine a final verdict—categorizing the trade as a major win, fair, minor loss, or a scam—providing you with a clear, actionable recommendation before you lock in your choice.</p>

      <p>If you are also interested in real-world shipping logistics, be sure to check out our <a href="/ups-shipping-calculator">UPS Shipping Calculator</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details>
        <summary>How is Blox Fruits trade value determined?</summary>
        <p>Trade values in Blox Fruits are primarily driven by community demand rather than in-game purchase prices (Beli or Robux). Highly sought-after fruits like Kitsune or Leopard hold massive trade value because players want to use them for PvP, whereas expensive but low-demand fruits like Gravity are often treated merely as "value-adds" to bridge price gaps.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Why does a trade show as 'Unfair' even if the Beli values match?</summary>
        <p>The in-game system only checks if the Beli value difference is within the maximum 40% difference rule. However, a trade can technically pass this check but be terrible in terms of actual community value (e.g., trading a high-demand Buddha for a low-demand Gravity). True trade equality is measured by community demand value, not Beli.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What is the most valuable fruit in Blox Fruits?</summary>
        <p>Values shift with updates, but generally, Mythical tier fruits like Kitsune, Dragon, and Leopard command the absolute highest trade values due to their extreme rarity, massive PvP dominance, and high visual appeal, making them the most sought-after items in the trading hubs.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Should I trade my Buddha fruit?</summary>
        <p>Buddha is widely considered the absolute best fruit for grinding levels and completing raids, granting it exceptionally high demand and a stable trade value far above its official 1.2M Beli cost. You should only trade a Buddha if you are receiving high-tier mythicals or specific gamepasses in return.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How often do Blox Fruits values change?</summary>
        <p>Values fluctuate very frequently based on major game updates, awakenings, balance changes, and trending YouTube showcases. When a new fruit or awakening is announced by the developers, its market value generally spikes significantly within hours.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    // Fruit Data Directory (Approximate community trade values represented numerically for calculation)
    const fruitData = [
      { id: "kitsune", name: "Kitsune", beli: 8000000, trade: 115000000 },
      { id: "dragon", name: "Dragon", beli: 3500000, trade: 90000000 },
      { id: "leopard", name: "Leopard", beli: 5000000, trade: 40000000 },
      { id: "trex", name: "T-Rex", beli: 2700000, trade: 20000000 },
      { id: "dough", name: "Dough", beli: 2800000, trade: 22000000 },
      { id: "mammoth", name: "Mammoth", beli: 2700000, trade: 12500000 },
      { id: "venom", name: "Venom", beli: 3000000, trade: 9000000 },
      { id: "control", name: "Control", beli: 3200000, trade: 8000000 },
      { id: "spirit", name: "Spirit", beli: 3400000, trade: 10000000 },
      { id: "buddha", name: "Buddha", beli: 1200000, trade: 7000000 },
      { id: "portal", name: "Portal", beli: 1900000, trade: 6000000 },
      { id: "rumble", name: "Rumble", beli: 2100000, trade: 5000000 },
      { id: "blizzard", name: "Blizzard", beli: 2400000, trade: 4500000 },
      { id: "sound", name: "Sound", beli: 1700000, trade: 3000000 },
      { id: "shadow", name: "Shadow", beli: 2900000, trade: 6000000 },
      { id: "gravity", name: "Gravity", beli: 2500000, trade: 1500000 },
      { id: "pain", name: "Pain", beli: 2300000, trade: 1500000 },
      { id: "phoenix", name: "Phoenix", beli: 1800000, trade: 2000000 },
      { id: "spider", name: "Spider", beli: 1500000, trade: 1200000 },
      { id: "love", name: "Love", beli: 1300000, trade: 1100000 },
      { id: "quake", name: "Quake", beli: 1000000, trade: 1000000 },
      { id: "magma", name: "Magma", beli: 850000, trade: 1200000 },
      { id: "light", name: "Light", beli: 650000, trade: 800000 },
      { id: "ghost", name: "Ghost", beli: 1200000, trade: 900000 },
      { id: "rubber", name: "Rubber", beli: 750000, trade: 600000 },
      { id: "barrier", name: "Barrier", beli: 800000, trade: 500000 },
      { id: "dark", name: "Dark", beli: 500000, trade: 500000 },
      { id: "sand", name: "Sand", beli: 420000, trade: 400000 },
      { id: "ice", name: "Ice", beli: 350000, trade: 450000 },
      { id: "falcon", name: "Falcon", beli: 300000, trade: 250000 },
      { id: "flame", name: "Flame", beli: 250000, trade: 300000 },
      { id: "spike", name: "Spike", beli: 180000, trade: 150000 },
      { id: "smoke", name: "Smoke", beli: 100000, trade: 100000 },
      { id: "bomb", name: "Bomb", beli: 80000, trade: 80000 },
      { id: "spring", name: "Spring", beli: 60000, trade: 60000 },
      { id: "chop", name: "Chop", beli: 30000, trade: 30000 },
      { id: "spin", name: "Spin", beli: 180000, trade: 180000 },
      { id: "rocket", name: "Rocket", beli: 5000, trade: 5000 }
    ];

    // Format numbers with commas
    function formatNumber(num) {
      return num.toString().replace(/\B(?=(\d{3})+(?!\d))/g, ",");
    }

    // Populate dropdowns
    function initDropdowns() {
      const selects = document.querySelectorAll('.fruit-dropdown');

      let optionsHtml = '<option value="">Select Fruit...</option>';
      fruitData.forEach(fruit => {
        optionsHtml += '<option value="' + fruit.id + '">' + fruit.name + '</option>';
      });

      selects.forEach(select => {
        select.innerHTML = optionsHtml;
        select.addEventListener('change', calculateTrade);
      });
    }

    function calculateTrade() {
      const offerSelects = document.querySelectorAll('.offer-dropdown');
      const requestSelects = document.querySelectorAll('.request-dropdown');

      let offerBeli = 0;
      let offerTrade = 0;
      let requestBeli = 0;
      let requestTrade = 0;

      let offerCount = 0;
      let requestCount = 0;

      // Calculate Offer Side
      offerSelects.forEach(select => {
        const val = select.value;
        if (val) {
          const fruit = fruitData.find(f => f.id === val);
          if (fruit) {
            offerBeli += fruit.beli;
            offerTrade += fruit.trade;
            offerCount++;
          }
        }
      });

      // Calculate Request Side
      requestSelects.forEach(select => {
        const val = select.value;
        if (val) {
          const fruit = fruitData.find(f => f.id === val);
          if (fruit) {
            requestBeli += fruit.beli;
            requestTrade += fruit.trade;
            requestCount++;
          }
        }
      });

      // Update UI Counters
      document.getElementById('offer-beli').textContent = formatNumber(offerBeli);
      document.getElementById('offer-trade').textContent = formatNumber(offerTrade);
      document.getElementById('request-beli').textContent = formatNumber(requestBeli);
      document.getElementById('request-trade').textContent = formatNumber(requestTrade);

      const verdictBanner = document.getElementById('trade-verdict');
      const detailsText = document.getElementById('trade-details');
      const beliIndicator = document.getElementById('beli-check-indicator');
      const beliText = document.getElementById('beli-check-text');

      // Reset if empty
      if (offerCount === 0 && requestCount === 0) {
        verdictBanner.className = 'verdict-banner';
        verdictBanner.textContent = 'Waiting for inputs...';
        detailsText.textContent = 'Please select at least one fruit on both sides to calculate the trade outcome.';
        beliIndicator.className = 'status-indicator';
        beliText.textContent = 'In-Game 40% Beli Check';
        return;
      }

      if (offerCount === 0 || requestCount === 0) {
        verdictBanner.className = 'verdict-banner verdict-neutral';
        verdictBanner.textContent = 'Incomplete Trade';
        detailsText.textContent = 'Both sides must have at least one fruit to perform a comparison calculation.';
        beliIndicator.className = 'status-indicator status-bad';
        beliText.textContent = 'Cannot complete trade in game (Missing Items)';
        return;
      }

      // Calculate 40% Beli Difference Rule (In-game mechanic)
      // The lower side must be at least 60% of the higher side
      let beliPasses = false;
      if (offerBeli === 0 || requestBeli === 0) {
          beliPasses = false;
      } else {
          const maxBeli = Math.max(offerBeli, requestBeli);
          const minBeli = Math.min(offerBeli, requestBeli);
          if (minBeli >= (maxBeli * 0.6)) {
              beliPasses = true;
          }
      }

      if (beliPasses) {
        beliIndicator.className = 'status-indicator status-good';
        beliText.textContent = 'Passes 40% Rule: Trade will go through in-game.';
      } else {
        beliIndicator.className = 'status-indicator status-bad';
        beliText.textContent = 'Fails 40% Rule: Value difference too high. Add junk fruits to balance.';
      }

      // Calculate Trade Verdict based on Community Value
      const difference = requestTrade - offerTrade;
      const ratio = requestTrade / offerTrade;

      if (ratio > 1.15) {
        verdictBanner.className = 'verdict-banner verdict-win';
        verdictBanner.textContent = 'BIG WIN (W)';
        detailsText.textContent = 'You are receiving significantly more value than you are offering. Accept this trade immediately if possible.';
      } else if (ratio >= 0.90 && ratio <= 1.15) {
        verdictBanner.className = 'verdict-banner verdict-fair';
        verdictBanner.textContent = 'FAIR TRADE (F)';
        detailsText.textContent = 'This is a balanced trade. Both sides are receiving relatively equal community value. Do this if you want the fruits.';
      } else if (ratio < 0.90 && ratio >= 0.70) {
        verdictBanner.className = 'verdict-banner verdict-loss';
        verdictBanner.textContent = 'SMALL LOSS (L)';
        detailsText.textContent = 'You are overpaying slightly. Only accept this trade if you desperately want the fruit they are offering.';
      } else {
        verdictBanner.className = 'verdict-banner verdict-bad';
        verdictBanner.textContent = 'MASSIVE L / SCAM';
        detailsText.textContent = 'You are getting completely ripped off. Do not accept this trade under any circumstances.';
      }
    }

    // Initialize on load
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', initDropdowns);
  </script>

